This game does not work on any of my Nexus TV boxes (running 7.1.1) and on my Nexus 6 (running 7.0). The app starts and I can go to options screen, but as soon as I try to start a game it freezes with no response (music is playing though). Tried on low, medium, and high grafix option - same issue. Email to developers bounced back. Need this refunded... do not buy it.

I have a Sharp AQUOS LC70UE30U with 4 bluetooth game controllers a bluetooth keyboard, mouse and a remote. We are unable to click on buttons on the starting screen with any of those devices so we are unable to use this game. The preview looks good and we'd probably like the game if we can get it to work. It is listed as compatible. We have many other games working with the same setup. Please fix this ASAP.

Excellent game, fun cross-platform multiplayer. Unfortunately, the most recent update causes the app to crash (on Nexus 7) when the main menu loads. Also, I'd love to have some form of cloud save across devices.

1- online playing no longer works reliably. most room not joinable.  2- the premium version did not bring over my data from the unpaid version (started character over) 3- on multiple occasions the game breaks. the most frustrating was when i beat 29 levels of wave attack, only for the 30th level to just break. unable to die or progress, this forced me to quit, once again, losing all progress. bummer.  fun game, will fix rating if these issues are resolved before i unsinstall it.   Its easy to beat this game and be left with nothing to do. it was much more fun when online worked. i would not recomend people buy this game as the free version is not glitchy
